# Instant Ink Direct Debit Billing Form UI Enhancements

## Description

Enhance the Direct Debit billing form UI to align with Instant Ink design standards.
The UI must match the updated Instant Ink design specifications.

## User Roles

- Instant Ink storefront member.
- The role listed above is not application specific.

## Scope

This update applies to the following MIDs:

- PGSdemo_instantink_at
- PGSdemo_instantink_be
- PGSdemo_instantink_de
- PGSdemo_instantink_it
- PGSdemo_instantink_fr
- PGSdemo_instantink_es
- PGSdemo_instantink_nl

## Requirement

Enhance the Direct Debit billing form UI to align with Instant Ink design standards.

## Business Value

Users get a consistent, modern, and user-friendly experience across regions.

## Acceptance Criteria

1. Typography
   - Use "Forma DJR UI" font across the billing form.

2. Checkbox
   - Checkbox size: 24px x 24px.
   - Label text font size: 16px.

3. Input Fields
   - Border radius: 12px.
   - Height: 48px.

   Unfilled state:
   - Font size: 16px.
   - Font color: #3D3D3D.

   Filled state:
   - Font size: 12px.
   - Font color: #3D3D3D.

4. Buttons

   Common properties:
   - Border radius: 8px.
   - Font size: 16px.
   - Height: 48px.

   Continue button:
   - Disabled state background: #E8E8E8.
   - Disabled state font color: #A3A3A3.
   - Enabled state background: #024AD8.
   - Enabled state font color: #FFFFFF.

   Back button:
   - Font color: #024AD8.
   - Border color: #024AD8.
   - Display alongside the Continue button.

   Cancel button:
   - Must be included, even if missing in design screenshots.
   - Align with the Continue button in responsive layout.

5. Layout
   - On larger screens, input fields should appear in the same row where applicable.
   - Continue, Back, and Cancel buttons should appear in the same row.

6. Localization and Translations
   - Authorization checkbox text must be displayed based on locale:
     - de/de, at/de
     - es/es
     - it/it
     - be/nl
     - be/fr
     - nl/nl
     - fr/fr
   - Provided translations must be implemented exactly as specified.

